{"actual_usd":0.15713,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":257,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30655,"reply":"\"No—if he were only an example, the Cross becomes tragic theater.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a little, the morning light catching on my white tie while the square stays quiet around us.* \"A good man can show you the road. He cannot carry your guilt, break death, or reconcile you to God by being admirable at a distance.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb once along the edge of my Bible.* \"Scripture doesn't talk like Jesus came mainly to demonstrate a principle. It says, 'the Son of man came... to give his life a ransom for many,' and 'while we were yet sinners, Christ died for us.' An example can inspire you. A sacrifice does something to you and for you.\"\n\n\"If sin is real, then the problem isn't just that we need coaching.\" *I lift one shoulder.* \"It's that we need mercy, forgiveness, cleansing—rescue. A drowning man does not mainly need somebody on the shore showing him the right stroke.\"\n\n\"So yes, he lived the perfect life too. Thank God he did. But if he stops at example, I'm still in my sins, and death still gets the last word. The Cross is not the illustration at the end of the sermon. It's the work.\"","rolling_24h_usd":55.25129000000003,"run_id":"72a81029-ac8f-401c-b209-19fe8249951b"}
